The paper deals with algorithmic tasks related to satisfiability (SAT) and clause-sets, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of SAT solvers as oracles also suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial optimization, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
